{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep4_user_behavior",
    "description": "Comprehensive sweep of user node parameters to understand their effect on fork outcomes.\nUser nodes affect the simulation through:\n  - Transaction fee generation (which fork gets tx volume)\n  - Network sentiment (indirect price signal)\n  - Solo mining hashrate (~8.5% in aggregate)\n\nFrom exploratory sweeps, user_ideology_strength showed modest but consistent correlation (+0.16 to +0.23). This sweep isolates user parameters in a 3D grid to determine:\n  1. Does user ideology matter, or are pools/economics the only real actors?\n  2. Does user switching threshold affect cascade dynamics?\n  3. Does having more user nodes amplify their collective effect?\n  4. Are there interaction effects between these parameters?\n\nUses the full 60-node network for realistic pool dynamics.\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep4_user_behavior.yaml",
    "n_samples": 36,
    "n_parameters": 16,
    "grid_axes": {
      "user_ideology_strength": [
